Introduction.name: Introduction
Introduction.content: # twitter-types Type definitions for Twitter API v2

typedefs.name: APIClientDisconnectedProblem
typedefs.description: Your client has gone away

typedefs.name: APIClientForbiddenProblem
typedefs.description: A problem that indicates your client is forbidden from making this request

typedefs.name: APIConnectionExceptionProblem
typedefs.description: A problem that indicates something is wrong with the connection

typedefs.name: APIDisallowedResourceProblem
typedefs.description: A problem that indicates that the resource requested violates the precepts of this API

typedefs.name: APIDuplicateRuleProblem
typedefs.description: The rule you have submitted is a duplicate

typedefs.name: APIFieldUnauthorizedProblem
typedefs.description: A problem that indicates that you are not allowed to see a particular field on a Tweet, User, etc

typedefs.name: APIFilteredTweetStreamRule
typedefs.description: A user-provided stream filtering rule

props.name: id
props.description: Unique identifier of this rule

props.name: tag
props.description: A tag meant for the labeling of user provided rules

props.name: value
props.description: The filter value of the rule

typedefs.name: APIGenericProblem
typedefs.description: A generic problem with no additional information beyond that provided by the HTTP status code

typedefs.name: APIInvalidRequestProblem
typedefs.description: A problem that indicates the request is invalid

typedefs.name: APIInvalidRuleProblem
typedefs.description: The rule you have submitted is invalid

props.name: created_at
props.description: Creation time of this list

props.name: description
props.description: The description of the list

props.name: follower_count
props.description: Number of users who follow this list

props.name: id
props.description: The id of the list

props.name: member_count
props.description: Number of users who are a member of this list

props.name: name
props.description: The name of the created list

props.name: owner_id
props.description: The user id of the owner of the list

props.name: private
props.description: Whether the list is private

typedefs.name: APIMedia
typedefs.description: https://developer.twitter.com/en/docs/twitter-api/data-dictionary/object-model/media

props.name: alt_text
props.description: The description of an image

props.name: duration_ms
props.description: The duration of the media content in milliseconds if it is of type `video`

props.name: height
props.description: The height of the media content in pixels

props.name: media_key
props.description: The unique identifier of the expanded media content

props.name: non_public_metrics
props.description:
Non-public engagement metrics for the media content at the time of the request.
Requires user context authentication. This field is only present for type `video`

props.name: organic_metrics
props.description:
Engagement metrics for the media content, tracked in an organic context, at the time of the request.
Requires user context authentication. This field is only present for type `video`

props.name: preview_image_url
props.description: The URL to the static placeholder preview of the media content

props.name: promoted_metrics
props.description:
Engagement metrics for the media content, tracked in a promoted context, at the time of the request.
Requires user context authentication. This field is only present for type `video`

props.name: public_metrics
props.description:
Public engagement metrics for the media content at the time of the request.
This field is only present for type `video`

props.name: type
props.description: The type of the media content

props.name: url
props.description: The url of the media content if it is of type `photo`

props.name: width
props.description: The width of the media content in pixels

typedefs.name: APIMediaNonPublicMetrics
typedefs.description: Non public metrics for a media of type `video`

props.name: playback_0_count
props.description: Number of users who made it through 0% of the video

props.name: playback_100_count
props.description: Number of users who made it through 100% of the video

props.name: playback_25_count
props.description: Number of users who made it through 25% of the video

props.name: playback_50_count
props.description: Number of users who made it through 50% of the video

props.name: playback_75_count
props.description: Number of users who made it through 75% of the video

typedefs.name: APIMediaPublicMetrics
typedefs.description: Public metrics for a media of type `video`

props.name: view_count
props.description: Number of times this video has been viewed

typedefs.name: APIOperationalDisconnectProblem
typedefs.description: You have been disconnected for operational reasons

typedefs.name: APIPlace
typedefs.description: https://developer.twitter.com/en/docs/twitter-api/data-dictionary/object-model/place

props.name: contained_within
props.description: The identifiers of known places that contain this place

props.name: country
props.description: The full-length name of the country this place belongs to

props.name: country_code
props.description: The `ISO Alpha-2` country code this place belongs to

props.name: full_name
props.description: A longer-form detailed name of this place

props.name: geo
props.description: Contains details about the place in `GeoJSON` format

props.name: id
props.description: The unique identifier of the expanded place, if this is a point of interest tagged in the Tweet

props.name: name
props.description: The short name of this place

props.name: place_type
props.description:
The particular type of information represented by this place information,
such as a city name, or a point of interest

typedefs.name: APIPoll
typedefs.description: https://developer.twitter.com/en/docs/twitter-api/data-dictionary/object-model/poll

props.name: duration_minutes
props.description: The total duration of the poll

props.name: end_datetime
props.description: The `ISO 8601` end date and time for the poll

props.name: id
props.description: The unique identifier of the poll

props.name: options
props.description: Contains objects describing each choice in the poll

props.name: voting_status
props.description: Indicates if this poll is still active and can receive votes, or if the voting is now closed

typedefs.name: APIResourceNotFoundProblem
typedefs.description: A problem that indicates that a given Tweet, User, etc. does not exist

typedefs.name: APIResourceUnauthorizedProblem
typedefs.description: A problem that indicates you are not allowed to see a particular Tweet, User, etc

typedefs.name: APIResourceUnavailableProblem
typedefs.description: A problem that indicates a particular Tweet, User, etc. is not available to you

typedefs.name: APIRulesCapProblem
typedefs.description: You have exceeded the maximum number of rules

props.name: created_at
props.description: Creation time of this Space

props.name: creator_id
props.description: The id of the user who created this space

props.name: host_ids
props.description: The unique identifier of the Users who are hosting this Space

props.name: id
props.description: The unique identifier of the requested Space

props.name: invited_user_ids
props.description:
The list of user IDs that were invited to join as speakers.
Usually, users in this list are invited to speak via the Invite user option

props.name: is_ticketed
props.description: Indicates whether this is a ticketed Space

props.name: lang
props.description: Language of the Space, if detected by Twitter. Returned as a `BCP47` language tag

props.name: participant_count
props.description: The current number of users in the Space, including Hosts and Speakers

props.name: scheduled_start
props.description:
Indicates the start time of a scheduled Space, as set by the creator of the Space.
This field is returned only if the Space has been scheduled; in other words,
if the field is returned, it means the Space is a scheduled Space

props.name: speaker_ids
props.description:
The list of users who were speaking at any point during the Space.
This list contains all the users in `invited_user_ids` in addition to
any user who requested to speak and was allowed via the Add speaker option

props.name: started_at
props.description: Indicates the actual start time of a Space

props.name: state
props.description: Indicates if the Space has started or will start in the future, or if it has ended

props.name: subscriber_count
props.description: The number of people who have either purchased a ticket or set a reminder for this space

props.name: title
props.description: The title of the Space as specified by the creator

props.name: updated_at
props.description: Specifies the date and time of the last update to any of the Space's metadata, such as its title or scheduled time

typedefs.name: APITweet
typedefs.description: https://developer.twitter.com/en/docs/twitter-api/data-dictionary/object-model/tweet

props.name: attachments
props.description: The type of attachments (if any) present in the Tweet

props.name: author_id
props.description: The unique identifier of the User who posted the Tweet

props.name: context_annotations
props.description: Contains context annotations for the Tweet

props.name: conversation_id
props.description: The ID of the original Tweet of the conversation (which includes direct replies, replies of replies)

props.name: created_at
props.description: The `ISO 8601` creation time of the Tweet

props.name: entities
props.description: The entities which have been parsed out of the text of the Tweet

props.name: geo
props.description: The details about the location tagged by the user in the Tweet, if they specified one

props.name: id
props.description: The unique identifier of the requested Tweet

props.name: in_reply_to_user_id
props.description:
If the Tweet is a reply, this field will contain the original Tweet’s author ID.
This will not necessarily always be the user directly mentioned in the Tweet

props.name: lang
props.description: The language of the Tweet, if detected by Twitter. Returned as a `BCP47` language tag

props.name: non_public_metrics
props.description:
Non-public engagement metrics for the Tweet at the time of the request.
Requires user context authentication

props.name: organic_metrics
props.description:
Engagement metrics tracked in an organic context for the Tweet at the time of the request.
Requires user context authentication

props.name: possibly_sensitive
props.description:
This field only surfaces when a Tweet contains a link. The meaning of the field doesn’t pertain
to the Tweet content itself, but instead it is an indicator that the URL contained in the Tweet
may contain content or media identified as sensitive content

props.name: promoted_metrics
props.description:
Engagement metrics tracked in a promoted context for the Tweet at the time of the request.
Requires user context authentication

props.name: public_metrics
props.description: Public engagement metrics for the Tweet at the time of the request

props.name: referenced_tweets
props.description: A list of Tweets this Tweet refers to. It will also include the related Tweet referenced to by its parent

props.name: reply_settings
props.description: Shows who can reply to the Tweet

props.name: source
props.description: The name of the app the user Tweeted from

props.name: text
props.description: The actual `UTF-8` text of the Tweet

props.name: withheld
props.description: When present, contains withholding details for withheld content

typedefs.name: APITweetWithheld
typedefs.description:
Indicates withholding details for
[withheld content](https://help.twitter.com/en/rules-and-policies/tweet-withheld-by-country)

props.name: copyright
props.description: Indicates if the content is being withheld for on the basis of copyright infringement

props.name: country_codes
props.description: Provides a list of countries where this content is not available

props.name: scope
props.description: Indicates whether the content being withheld is the `tweet` or a `user`

typedefs.name: APIUnsupportedAuthenticationProblem
typedefs.description: A problem that indicates that the authentication used is not supported

typedefs.name: APIUsageCapExceededProblem
typedefs.description: A problem that indicates that a usage cap has been exceeded

typedefs.name: APIUser
typedefs.description: The Twitter User object

props.name: created_at
props.description: The UTC datetime that the user account was created on Twitter

props.name: description
props.description: The text of this user's profile description (also known as bio), if the user provided one

props.name: entities
props.description: Contains details about text that has a special meaning in the user's description

props.name: id
props.description: The unique identifier of the user

props.name: location
props.description:
The location specified in the user's profile, if the user provided one. As this is a freeform value,
it may not indicate a valid location, but it may be fuzzily evaluated when performing searches with
location queries

props.name: name
props.description:
The name of the user, as they’ve defined it on their profile. Not necessarily a person’s name.
Typically capped at `50` characters, but subject to change

props.name: pinned_tweet_id
props.description: The unique identifier of this user's pinned Tweet

props.name: profile_image_url
props.description: The URL to the profile image for this user, as shown on the user's profile

props.name: protected
props.description: Indicates if this user has chosen to protect their Tweets (in other words, if this user's Tweets are private)

props.name: public_metrics
props.description: Contains details about activity for this user

props.name: url
props.description: The URL specified in the user's profile, if present

props.name: username
props.description:
The Twitter screen name, handle, or alias that this user identifies themselves with. Usernamesare unique but
subject to change. Typically a maximum of `15` characters long, but some historical accounts may exist with longer
names

props.name: verified
props.description: Indicates if this user is a verified Twitter User

props.name: withheld
props.description: Contains withholding details for withheld content, if applicable

typedefs.name: APIUserWithheld
typedefs.description:
Indicates withholding details for
[withheld content](https://help.twitter.com/en/rules-and-policies/tweet-withheld-by-country)

props.name: country_codes
props.description: Provides a list of countries where this content is not available

props.name: scope
props.description: Indicates that the content being withheld is a `user`
